25:58.508 --> 26:00.776
In the background. You were
practically glowing about it.

26:00.810 --> 26:02.444
That's because
I accomplished something.

26:02.479 --> 26:03.879
It had nothing to do with you.

26:03.914 --> 26:06.582
No, see, it actually has
everything to do with me.

26:06.616 --> 26:08.984
Every step that you take
in this city is fueled

26:09.019 --> 26:11.353
by all of the hate
that we gave you.

26:11.388 --> 26:14.156
All of that ambition is just
you trying to prove us wrong.

26:14.191 --> 26:15.958
Which is fine, Rachel.
I mean, whatever works for you.

26:15.992 --> 26:17.526
Just don't try
to say that it isn't.

26:17.561 --> 26:19.094
You know what? Why don't we just
chill for a second, please.

26:19.129 --> 26:20.896
Okay, I'll make espresso.
You know what?

26:20.931 --> 26:22.198
You can't handle it.

26:22.232 --> 26:24.166
You can't handle
that I have made it,

26:24.201 --> 26:26.735
and you are just begging
to be my understudy.

26:27.771 --> 26:29.972
Okay, you know what?

26:30.006 --> 26:32.374
Just admit that even with all
of your years of singing lessons

26:32.409 --> 26:35.878
and dancing lessons and
only-child adoration

26:35.912 --> 26:37.479
from your gay
Broadway dads that I

26:37.514 --> 26:39.448
am just as good as you.

26:39.482 --> 26:42.151
Unlike you, I can be popular
in high school and still

26:42.185 --> 26:43.419
make it big after graduation.

26:43.453 --> 26:45.621
Just admit that no matter
what you do,

26:45.655 --> 26:47.189
or how far you go,

26:47.224 --> 26:48.958
you will never be able
to scratch that itch.

26:48.992 --> 26:52.061
You will never be able to look
down on me and redeem yourself.

26:52.095 --> 26:53.696
Because I was better
than you then,

26:53.730 --> 26:55.364
and I'm always gonna
be better than you.

26:55.398 --> 26:57.299
You are short,
you are awful, and

26:57.334 --> 26:58.667
that is never going to change.
(grunts)

26:58.702 --> 27:00.703
(Kurt gasps)

27:02.772 --> 27:06.075
I think you should move out.

27:06.109 --> 27:07.243
I agree.
(phone buzzing)

27:07.277 --> 27:08.744
This is crazy!
We're friends!

27:08.778 --> 27:10.045
Not really.

27:10.080 --> 27:12.548
(phone buzzing)

27:14.951 --> 27:16.485
Hello?

27:16.519 --> 27:18.721
Yeah, good.

27:18.755 --> 27:22.091
Okay. Well, thank you
for letting me know so soon.

27:22.125 --> 27:24.593
Bye.

27:24.628 --> 27:26.962
I'll see you
at rehearsals, Berry.

27:26.997 --> 27:28.764
I'm your new understudy.

27:35.572 --> 27:39.274
Welcome idiots to the McKinley
High valedictorian speech-off.

27:39.309 --> 27:41.310
♪

27:43.146 --> 27:45.147
♪

27:57.594 --> 28:00.496
Your job today is to decide
which of these speeches

28:00.530 --> 28:02.865
is slightly less awful.

28:02.899 --> 28:04.800
That being said,
allow me to present

28:04.834 --> 28:07.336
absolutely no one's
favorite New Direction!...

28:07.370 --> 28:08.971
Tina Cohen-Chang.

28:09.005 --> 28:11.006
♪

28:17.714 --> 28:19.047
(feedback squeals)

28:19.082 --> 28:21.617
My fellow graduates,

28:21.651 --> 28:23.786
I feel like I was
a different person

28:23.820 --> 28:27.122
when I first arrived at McKinley
High School four years ago.

28:27.157 --> 28:29.224
I was a goth chick

28:29.259 --> 28:32.394
who was so intent
on pushing people away

28:32.429 --> 28:34.630
that I pretended
to have a stutter,

28:34.664 --> 28:37.800
which I now understand
wasn't even that convincing.

28:37.834 --> 28:39.334
I wasn't even

28:39.369 --> 28:41.069
good at stuttering.

28:41.104 --> 28:45.474
But then, something
in my life changed.

28:45.508 --> 28:49.378
Someone, actually.

28:49.412 --> 28:53.015
In fact...
that someone changed me.

28:54.517 --> 28:57.419
And that person's name
is Artie Abrams.

28:58.688 --> 29:01.390
Artie, wait. I'm really sorry.
It was an accident.

29:01.424 --> 29:03.392
You're still one of
my best friends, Artie.

29:03.426 --> 29:04.660
I know you know that.

29:04.694 --> 29:06.161
Ditto.

29:06.196 --> 29:09.231
Artie has taught me
how to not only be myself,

29:09.265 --> 29:11.200
but he's an inspiration to
high school students everywhere.

29:11.234 --> 29:13.235
ARTIE: <i>Sure, I've
experienced adversity.</i>

29:13.269 --> 29:15.404
One Christmas, I was given
a pair of mechanical legs

29:15.438 --> 29:17.739
that allowed me to walk for an
hour before they promptly broke.

29:17.774 --> 29:20.008
But I've never been so humbled
as I was

29:20.043 --> 29:22.544
the moment Tina Cohen-Chang
wiped the slushie off

29:22.579 --> 29:24.880
of her gown and triumphantly
returned to the stage

29:24.914 --> 29:26.882
to claim her rightful crown
as prom queen.

29:26.916 --> 29:28.984
That is why I respectfully

29:29.018 --> 29:30.385
withdraw myself
from consideration,

29:30.420 --> 29:32.354
and ask that Tina be named
this year's valedictorian.

29:32.388 --> 29:35.357
I believe he should be given the
title of class valedictorian.

29:35.391 --> 29:37.059
(sniffling)
God, this can't be happening.

29:37.093 --> 29:38.360
TINA:
Is it a bridge too far

29:38.394 --> 29:40.662
to call Artie Abrams
an American hero?

29:40.697 --> 29:42.130
I think not.

29:42.165 --> 29:44.399
ARTIE:
<i>It's no exaggeration to say</i>

29:44.434 --> 29:45.801
that Tina took my broken body
in her arms

29:45.835 --> 29:47.169
and taught me how to love.

29:47.203 --> 29:49.905
And as he strains to push
his wheelchair up that ramp,

29:49.939 --> 29:52.741
the ghosts of fallen heroes
follow close behind.

29:52.775 --> 29:55.978
Rosa Parks, Mahatma Gandhi.

29:56.012 --> 29:59.248
Artie Abrams holds high
the torch of dignity.

29:59.282 --> 30:02.518
So please, respected judges,
cast your lot for Tina.

30:02.552 --> 30:05.120
I beseech you, vote for Artie.

30:05.154 --> 30:08.891
Tina Cohen-Chang, teammate,
sometime lover,

30:08.925 --> 30:11.159
patriot, friend.

30:11.194 --> 30:13.228
Thank you.

30:13.263 --> 30:14.396
Thank you.

30:14.430 --> 30:15.631
What a treacly, stomach-turning

30:15.665 --> 30:18.433
waste of everybody's time.

30:18.468 --> 30:20.002
I hate you both.

30:20.036 --> 30:22.671
The judges will now make
their decision

30:22.705 --> 30:24.673
while I find a
wastebasket to dry-heave

30:24.707 --> 30:27.809
mouthfuls of yellow bile into.

30:41.991 --> 30:43.458
What are you doing?

30:43.493 --> 30:44.793
Putting makeup on.

30:44.827 --> 30:46.228
I have some bruising on my cheek

30:46.262 --> 30:47.742
I'd like to cover up
before rehearsal.

30:47.764 --> 30:49.565
You may not know this because
you haven't been interested

30:49.599 --> 30:50.899
in Broadway
since the day we met,

30:50.934 --> 30:52.367
but the star gets
her own vanity.

30:52.402 --> 30:53.502
There is a perfectly fine

30:53.536 --> 30:55.404
bathroom mirror upstairs
for the understudy.

30:55.438 --> 30:57.606
So sorry, I totally forgot
how much room you need

30:57.640 --> 30:59.841
for all that hooker makeup
you plaster on every day.

30:59.876 --> 31:01.343
I will totally slap you again.

31:01.377 --> 31:03.178
I would love for things
to get physical.

31:03.212 --> 31:05.147
I will hit you so hard that
you won't be able to wake up

31:05.181 --> 31:07.449
until you're old enough
to be <i>Funny Lady.</i>

31:07.483 --> 31:09.117
You will never play this part;
I know you're planning

31:09.152 --> 31:10.953
on getting all <i>Showgirls</i> crazy
on me and pushing me

31:10.987 --> 31:12.154
down the stairs
and poisoning my oatmeal,

31:12.188 --> 31:13.522
but you're gonna have
to kill me first,

31:13.556 --> 31:15.316
and even then,
I will come back from the dead

31:15.325 --> 31:17.526
and I will play this part
just to spite you.

31:17.560 --> 31:18.527
Zombie Fanny?

31:18.561 --> 31:20.295
Ghost Fanny, actually.

31:20.330 --> 31:21.630
What's this?

31:21.664 --> 31:23.532
Fighting? No, no, no.

31:23.566 --> 31:24.833
No way, no fighting.

31:24.867 --> 31:26.368
Okay, Rupert,
this isn't gonna work.

31:26.402 --> 31:27.936
Santana and I have a past.

31:27.971 --> 31:30.272
Which besides her
being incredibly talented,

31:30.306 --> 31:31.473
is why she is here.

31:31.507 --> 31:33.775
If you want to fill this house,

31:33.810 --> 31:35.243
we need all the press
we can get.

31:35.278 --> 31:36.912
I've got Pat Healy
from the <i>New York Times,</i>

31:36.946 --> 31:38.614
David Cote from <i>Time Out,</i>

31:38.648 --> 31:39.748
Adam Hetrick

31:39.782 --> 31:42.417
from playbill.com
all begging me

31:42.452 --> 31:44.052
to break the story
of the two girls

31:44.087 --> 31:45.487
from the same high school
in Ohio

31:45.521 --> 31:47.522
who made it big in the
same Broadway show.

31:47.557 --> 31:49.257
Two old friends

31:49.292 --> 31:53.128
finding fame, love and fortune
in the big city. Hell of a hook.

31:53.162 --> 31:56.531
You're both gonna get plenty
of attention individually,

31:56.566 --> 31:59.234
but it is a fact, as a team,

31:59.268 --> 32:01.203
you'll be twice as famous.

32:01.237 --> 32:03.572
From now on, I want the two
of you joined at the hip.

32:03.606 --> 32:05.574
You both need to know every
move Fanny makes in the show,

32:05.608 --> 32:06.875
starting with scene 14.

32:06.909 --> 32:09.444
Rachel, you'll run through
it first, then Santana.

32:09.479 --> 32:10.519
I don't know what happened

32:10.546 --> 32:11.813
between the two of
you in the past.

32:11.848 --> 32:13.115
Honestly, I don't really care.

32:13.149 --> 32:15.884
It's all...
puppy dogs and rainbows

32:15.918 --> 32:18.487
from now till this show closes.

32:19.489 --> 32:21.089
(sighs heavily)

32:22.959 --> 32:24.826
Well...

32:24.861 --> 32:26.428
at least we know who
the rainbow is,

32:26.462 --> 32:27.963
and who's the dog.

32:27.997 --> 32:30.098
Bathroom's upstairs!

32:30.133 --> 32:32.134
(The Police's
"Every Breath You Take" begins)

32:42.145 --> 32:45.147
♪ Every breath you take ♪

32:45.181 --> 32:48.984
♪ And every move you make ♪

32:49.018 --> 32:51.620
♪ Every bond you break ♪

32:51.654 --> 32:53.622
♪ Every step you take ♪

32:53.656 --> 32:57.592
♪ I'll be watching you ♪

32:57.627 --> 33:01.530
♪ Every single day ♪

33:01.564 --> 33:05.634
♪ And every word you say ♪

33:05.668 --> 33:07.569
♪ Every game you play ♪

33:07.603 --> 33:09.471
♪ Every night you stay ♪

33:09.505 --> 33:12.741
♪ I'll be watching you ♪

33:13.776 --> 33:17.245
♪ Oh, can't you see? ♪

33:17.280 --> 33:21.249
♪ You belong to me ♪

33:21.284 --> 33:25.620
♪ How my poor heart aches ♪

33:25.655 --> 33:29.591
♪ With every step you take ♪

33:29.625 --> 33:33.695
♪ Every move you make ♪

33:33.730 --> 33:37.566
♪ And every vow you break ♪

33:37.600 --> 33:39.634
♪ Every smile you fake ♪

33:39.669 --> 33:41.670
♪ Every claim you stake ♪

33:41.704 --> 33:44.639
BOTH:
♪ I'll be watching you ♪

33:47.210 --> 33:51.113
♪ Since you've gone, I've been
lost without a trace ♪

33:51.147 --> 33:55.584
♪ I dream at night,
I can only see your face ♪

33:55.618 --> 33:59.888
♪ I look around,
but it's you I can't replace ♪

33:59.922 --> 34:03.558
♪ I feel so cold,
and I long for your embrace ♪

34:03.593 --> 34:05.327
BOTH:
♪ I keep crying ♪

34:05.361 --> 34:09.364
♪ Baby, by, pase... ♪

34:15.605 --> 34:17.505
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

34:17.540 --> 34:20.208
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh... ♪

34:20.243 --> 34:23.612
♪ Ooh, ooh-ooh,
Ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

34:23.646 --> 34:27.849
♪ Every breath you take,
every move you make ♪

34:27.884 --> 34:29.451
♪ Every bond you break ♪

34:29.485 --> 34:31.520
♪ Every step you take ♪

34:31.554 --> 34:35.757
BOTH: ♪ Every single day,
every word you say ♪

34:35.792 --> 34:37.826
♪ Every game you play ♪

34:37.860 --> 34:39.860
♪ Every night you stay ♪

34:39.896 --> 34:43.697
BOTH: ♪ Every move you make,
every vow you break ♪

34:43.733 --> 34:45.734
♪ Every smile you fake ♪

34:45.768 --> 34:47.636
♪ I'll be watching ♪

34:47.670 --> 34:51.172
BOTH: ♪ Every single day,
every word you say ♪

34:51.206 --> 34:54.042
♪ Every game you play ♪

34:54.076 --> 34:57.746
♪ I'll be watching you. ♪

35:11.060 --> 35:13.128
Ah, T. Rex?

35:13.162 --> 35:16.798
Oh, be still my glam heart.

35:16.833 --> 35:19.568
You know, there's this amazing
flea market in Park Slope

35:19.602 --> 35:20.735
- that we should go to.
- Ooh.

35:20.770 --> 35:22.204
I will help you pick out

35:22.238 --> 35:24.372
the perfect records
to add to your collection.

35:24.407 --> 35:25.740
I'm, uh, kind of magic
like that.

35:25.775 --> 35:29.244
And I am kind of magic
at baking prepackaged goods

35:29.278 --> 35:30.946
with extra glazing.

35:30.980 --> 35:32.380
- Aw...
- Yes!

35:32.415 --> 35:33.615
That looks amazing.

35:33.649 --> 35:35.884
(chuckles)

35:35.918 --> 35:37.118
You know, Kurt...

35:37.153 --> 35:39.221
you know, this might sound
a little bit weird,

35:39.255 --> 35:41.890
but, um, I'm so glad
that we've met.

35:41.924 --> 35:43.391
I mean,

35:43.426 --> 35:44.759
you're the first gay friend
that I've made

35:44.794 --> 35:46.127
in the city that's not crazy

35:46.162 --> 35:48.496
or just trying to hook up.

35:48.531 --> 35:50.799
But I do know what you're doing.

35:50.833 --> 35:53.134
What's that?

35:53.169 --> 35:55.937
I'm not trying
to take over you band, man.

35:55.972 --> 35:57.672
That's what
you're thinking, right?

35:57.707 --> 36:00.107
I mean, that's why we've been
spending so much time together?

36:01.978 --> 36:03.178
You are kind of magic.

36:03.212 --> 36:04.746
I'm sorry,
I-I just wanted to,

36:04.780 --> 36:05.847
you know, figure out,

36:05.882 --> 36:07.215
exactly what your deal was.

36:07.250 --> 36:08.617
Well, the deal is this.

36:08.651 --> 36:10.952
You guys are awesome.

36:10.987 --> 36:12.954
You're good people,
you're talented

36:12.989 --> 36:14.723
and, you know what?
So am I.

36:14.757 --> 36:17.225
So let's not be
these, like, smiley frenemies

36:17.260 --> 36:18.360
that backstab each other.

36:18.394 --> 36:20.662
Let's go out
and kick ass together.

36:20.696 --> 36:23.498
I mean, I'm a part of your band.

36:23.532 --> 36:26.368
Yeah, you are.

36:26.402 --> 36:27.369
Okay, let's document
this moment.

36:27.403 --> 36:28.503
Shall we? Great.
Yes, yes.

36:28.537 --> 36:30.417
I think this calls
for a Pamela Lansbury selfie.

36:33.276 --> 36:34.910
Oh! See...
I was still chewing.

36:34.944 --> 36:36.444
Oh, sorry, let's take
a look, it could be...

36:36.479 --> 36:37.979
Yeah, no, we're doing
that again...

36:38.014 --> 36:39.781
Yeah, that's awful.
We're going that again, okay?

36:39.815 --> 36:41.549
One, two... Be super cute.

36:43.019 --> 36:45.086
Aw, cute!
(laughs)

36:45.121 --> 36:47.255
(gasps) Oh!

36:47.290 --> 36:49.591
(school bell ringing)

36:49.625 --> 36:51.726
Well, the judges have spoken.

36:51.761 --> 36:53.461
And?
Congratulations, morons.

36:53.496 --> 36:55.096
You split the vote.
It's a tie.

36:55.131 --> 36:56.131
Are you serious?

36:56.165 --> 36:58.133
Yes, I am, Make-a-Wish.

36:58.167 --> 36:59.801
Now I have no choice

36:59.835 --> 37:01.469
but to make you
co-salutatorians.

37:01.504 --> 37:03.805
And elevate the student
ranked number three

37:03.839 --> 37:05.140
to the class valedictorian.

37:05.174 --> 37:06.141
Who?

37:06.175 --> 37:07.642
Blaine Anderson.

37:07.677 --> 37:09.210
What?
What?!

37:09.245 --> 37:11.846
I'm really sorry, guys.
I feel terrible.

37:11.881 --> 37:13.648
Don't be, if we can't
be valedictorian,

37:13.683 --> 37:14.716
we're glad it's you.

37:14.750 --> 37:16.351
No, but you two deserve it.

37:16.385 --> 37:18.553
I mean, come on, you guys have
a higher grade point average.

37:18.587 --> 37:20.221
I know this sounds
like a humble brag.

37:20.256 --> 37:21.489
But honestly,
I feel like sometimes

37:21.524 --> 37:23.191
things just get handed to me.

37:24.226 --> 37:26.127
Really? Hmm.
I never noticed that.

37:26.162 --> 37:27.429
You know, like, how Mr. Shue

37:27.463 --> 37:28.797
gives me more solos
than anyone, and...

37:28.831 --> 37:30.432
BECKY:
Blade gay Blaine!

37:30.466 --> 37:33.001
When did you break-up
with Pancake Face?

37:33.035 --> 37:34.669
Uh, Becky, I'd really
appreciate it

37:34.704 --> 37:38.239
if you didn't call my
fiancé "Pancake Face."

37:38.274 --> 37:40.241
And no, we're not broken up.

37:40.276 --> 37:43.011
Yeah, you are.

37:43.045 --> 37:45.046
(quietly):
What?

37:47.683 --> 37:51.386
Um, that's a...
that's a great photo, Becky.

37:51.420 --> 37:53.288
But don't worry.

37:53.322 --> 37:54.356
Kurt and Elliot are
just friends.

37:54.390 --> 37:56.091
Just friends, my ass.

37:56.125 --> 37:58.893
Speaking of ass...

37:58.928 --> 37:59.928
Pancake Face is getting some.

37:59.962 --> 38:01.963
Oh, snap!

38:01.998 --> 38:04.299
(weak laugh)

38:08.762 --> 38:10.702
Tina and Artie have both
demurred from having solos

38:10.727 --> 38:12.294
at Nationals,
so we're still looking

38:12.329 --> 38:13.596
for someone to step up.

38:13.630 --> 38:15.631
Uh, Mr. Shue?
You already have a solo, Blaine.

38:15.665 --> 38:17.099
Thank you, Tina.

38:17.134 --> 38:19.769
This is about something else.

38:19.803 --> 38:21.103
As you may have all heard,

38:21.138 --> 38:23.105
I have been asked, oddly,

38:23.140 --> 38:25.174
to be valedictorian this year.

38:25.208 --> 38:26.942
And so, I thought,
instead of boring everybody

38:26.977 --> 38:28.611
with the traditional
valedictorian speech

38:28.645 --> 38:30.246
where I tell people to follow
their dreams

38:30.280 --> 38:31.714
and blah, blah,
blah, blah, blah,

38:31.748 --> 38:33.249
I could actually affect people
by singing.

38:33.283 --> 38:34.683
So I was hoping
you guys could help me

38:34.718 --> 38:36.786
brainstorm
some graduation songs.

38:36.820 --> 38:38.120
I cannot wait to watch

38:38.155 --> 38:40.156
Principal Sylvester
assassinate you.

38:42.893 --> 38:45.895
Look, I know you guys
both really wanted it.

38:47.164 --> 38:49.165
That's why I want both
of you to sing with me.

38:49.199 --> 38:52.268
Whatever song we pick,
we should pick together.

38:52.302 --> 38:53.836
And you should both
definitely have solos.

38:53.870 --> 38:55.437
And, Tina, we could
film rehearsal

38:55.472 --> 38:56.605
and send it to Brown.

38:56.640 --> 38:58.274
And they're so artsy
and progressive

38:58.308 --> 39:00.042
that I'm sure once they see it,
they're just gonna open up

39:00.076 --> 39:01.677
those Van Winkle gates,
looking for you.

39:01.711 --> 39:03.879
They better open them
really wide.

39:03.914 --> 39:05.281
Oh, Blainy Days.

39:05.315 --> 39:06.982
Well, if we're gonna go down,

39:07.017 --> 39:09.118
I'm honored to go
down together.

39:09.152 --> 39:10.653
Yes! Right! That's
that spirit I like!

39:10.687 --> 39:12.354
(all chatting happily)

39:12.389 --> 39:14.056
We all can't live here anymore.

39:14.090 --> 39:15.457
One of us has to go.

39:15.492 --> 39:16.992
I've paid rent here
for three months.

39:17.027 --> 39:19.495
And even though I never
actually got to have a bed,

39:19.529 --> 39:21.096
uh, I have squatter's rights.

39:21.131 --> 39:22.431
Kurt, you're the deciding vote.

39:22.465 --> 39:24.200
Oh, well, then I guess
I should pack my stuff now.

